        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="355"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <head>355. Memorandum From <persName corresp="#p_quinn-kennth-m">Kenneth M.
                        Quinn</persName> of the National Security Council Staff to the President’s
                    Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_scowcroft-brent"
                        >Scowcroft</persName>), Washington, October 8, 1976.<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d355fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r"
                            >Ford</persName> Library, National Security Adviser, Presidential
                        Country Files for East Asia and the Pacific, Box 15, Philippines (5).
                        Secret; Sensitive. Sent for information. <persName
                            corresp="#p_scowcroft-brent">Scowcroft</persName> initialed the upper
                        right hand corner of the document. Theodore Shackley, the Associate Deputy
                        Director for Operations at the <gloss target="#t_cia">CIA</gloss>, produced
                        a memorandum for the record, October 4, describing the meeting between
                            <persName corresp="#p_romulo-carlos">Romulo</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_bush-george-hw">Bush</persName>. ( Central Intelligence
                        Agency, OPI 10 [Executive Registry], Job 79M00467A, Box 23, Folder Number
                        15, P – 9: Philippines [426])</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d355fn2">[<hi rend="italic">text not
                            declassified in time for publication</hi>]</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1976-10-08">October 8, 1976</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">text not declassified in time for publication</hi>]</p>
            </div>
